node.title: David Parker first New Zealand MP to get Covid-19
node.description: Environment Minister David Parker is the first MP to report having tested positive for Covid-19.
node.content:
["Environment Minister David Parker is the first MP to report having tested positive for Covid-19.", "", "
Labour MP David Parker Photo: RNZ / Angus Dreaver
", "In a tweet, Parker said he was isolating at home after testing positive on Sunday, had minor symptoms and was "not feeling too bad".", "He had not been in the Beehive since last Monday, so was not with other MPs or staff while infectious, he said.", "Parker, 62, is also Attorney-General, Revenue Minister, Minister of Oceans and Fisheries, and Associate Finance Minister."]
